5.14 â€˜@urlâ€™, â€˜@uref{URL[, TEXT][, REPLACEMENT]}â€™
================================================

â€˜@urlâ€™ produces a reference to a uniform resource locator (URL). It
takes one mandatory argument, the URL, and two optional arguments which
control the text that is displayed.  In HTML and PDF output, â€˜@urlâ€™
produces a link you can follow.  (To merely indicate a URL without
creating a link people can follow, use â€˜@indicateurlâ€™, *note*
