   In printed output, however, the â€˜@small...â€™ commands typeset text in
a smaller font than the non-small example commands.  Thus, for instance,
code examples can contain longer lines and still fit on a page without
needing to be rewritten.

   Mark the end of a â€˜@small...â€™ block with a corresponding â€˜@end
small...â€™.  For example, pair â€˜@smallexampleâ€™ with â€˜@end smallexampleâ€™.

   Here is an example of the font used by the â€˜@smallexampleâ€™ command
