     @unnumbered Variable Index

     @printindex vr

     @node Concept Index
     @unnumbered Concept Index

     @printindex cp

   The text â€˜Indexâ€™ needs to appear in the name of the node containing
the index for the index to be found by Info readers.

   If you have more than one index, we recommend placing the concept
index last.

   Other details of index output in output formats:

   â€¢ As part of the process of creating a printed manual with TeX, you
     run a program called â€˜texindexâ€™ (*note* Hardcopy with TeX::) to sort
     the raw data to produce a sorted index file.  The sorted index file
