          * First index entry:   Top.   (line  7)

   â€¢ In plain text output, â€˜@printindexâ€™ formatting is usually similar
     to a menu in Info, showing the line number of each entry relative
     to the start of the file.

   â€¢ In HTML output, â€˜@printindexâ€™ produces links to the index entries.

   â€¢ In DocBook and LaTeX output, it simply records the index to be
     printed.


