11.1 Special Characters: Inserting @ {} , \ # &
===============================================

â€˜@â€™ and curly braces are the basic special characters in Texinfo.  To
insert these characters so they appear in text, you must put an â€˜@â€™ in
front of these characters to prevent Texinfo from misinterpreting them.
