â€˜@mathâ€™ (*note* Inserting Math::).  In this case, â€˜@\â€™ or â€˜\backslashâ€™
produce a "math" backslash (from the math symbol font), while
â€˜@backslashchar{}â€™ produces a typewriter backslash as usual.

   Although â€˜@backslashchar{}â€™ can be used nearly anywhere, there is no
need for it except in these unusual cases.


