12.4 â€˜@allowcodebreaksâ€™: Control Line Breaks in â€˜@codeâ€™
=======================================================

Ordinarily, TeX considers breaking lines at â€˜-â€™ and â€˜_â€™ characters
within â€˜@codeâ€™ and related commands (*note* @code::), more or less as if
they were "empty" hyphenation points.

