13.1 The Template for a Definition
==================================

     @deffn CATEGORY NAME ARGUMENTS...
     BODY-OF-DEFINITION
     @end deffn

The â€˜@deffnâ€™ command is used for definitions of entities that resemble
functions--entities that may take arguments.  Write the â€˜@deffnâ€™ command
at the beginning of a line and follow it on the same line by the
category of the entity, the name of the entity itself, and its arguments
(if any).  Then write the body of the definition on succeeding lines.
Finally, end the definition with an â€˜@end deffnâ€™ command written on a
line of its own.

For example,

     @deffn Command forward-word count
