completely, and use â€˜\â€™ in the TeX commands, by delineating a region
with the â€˜@texâ€™ and â€˜@end texâ€™ commands.  All plain TeX commands and
category codes are restored within a â€˜@texâ€™ region.  The sole exception
is that the â€˜@â€™ character still introduces a command, so that â€˜@end texâ€™
can be recognized.  Texinfo processors will not output material in such
a region unless TeX output is being produced.

