16.4 â€˜@alias NEW=EXISTINGâ€™
==========================

The â€˜@aliasâ€™ command defines a new command to be just like an existing
one.  This is useful for defining additional markup names, thus
preserving additional semantic information in the input even though the
output result may be the same.

   Write the â€˜@aliasâ€™ command on a line by itself, followed by the new
