â€˜gcc_html/â€™.  The subdirectory name is based on â€˜@setfilenameâ€™ or on the
input file name (*note* Setting the Output File Name::).

In any case, the top-level output file within the directory is always
named â€˜index.htmlâ€™.

   Monolithic output (â€˜--no-splitâ€™) is named according to
â€˜@setfilenameâ€™, if present (with any â€˜.infoâ€™ extension replaced with
â€˜.htmlâ€™), â€˜--outputâ€™ (the argument is used literally), or based on the
input file name as a last resort (*note* Setting the Output File Name::).


