     option is ignored by â€˜makeinfoâ€™ if â€˜@paragraphindent asisâ€™ is in
     effect.

â€˜insertâ€™
     Include normal paragraph indentation.  This respects the paragraph
     indentation set by a â€˜@paragraphindentâ€™ command (*note*
     @paragraphindent::).

   â€˜@firstparagraphindentâ€™ is ignored for HTML and DocBook output.

   It is best to write the â€˜@firstparagraphindentâ€™ command before the
end-of-header line at the beginning of a Texinfo file, so the region
formatting commands indent paragraphs as specified.  *Note* Start of
